column1: # Weekly cases of chicken pox in Ontario; Canada; 1924-89

# Note: the weekly chickenpox cases were not reported - to Statistics Canada - between 1959-1986.  Weekly chickenpox cases for Ontario were obtained from spreadsheets held by the Ontario Ministry of Health.

# When using this dataset please acknowledge the valuable help given by: Richard Trudeau (Chief of Health Statistics; Statistics Canada) who gave us access to data held by Statistics Canada; Glen Gagnon (Reference Librarian) for assistance in finding data at Statistics Canada; and Angie Fazzone who helped by finding data in the Ontario Ministry of Health archives.
